@192 = ~Talessyr's Potion Log~
@193 = ~This book contains written information about all potions and their usage or purpose by Talessyr Tranth. It contains information that Talessyr was contacted by her brother, Iltar, to prevent caravans from stopping at Cragmyr Keep by any means necessary letting the blame fall on the Flaming Fist. She resolved to hire rogues and have them conduct illegal "caravan inspections" on all southward caravans disguides as Flaming Fist officers. The resonance stones, obtained from a business acquintance of hers, were to be hidden in all the caravans and the disguised rogues amplified the suggestion spell places in the stones. It is a definite proof that Iltar and his sister, Talessyr, has been behind the trade block. You should hold on to this book.

Weight: 2~



@194 = ~Letter~
@195 = ~Dear sister,
I, and Amn, are in a dire need of your help. The war between Amn and Baldur's Gate now seems imminent, and Nashkel is poorly defended against any attacks from the north. Due to the Sothillisian War, Amn cannot send enough troops to defend Nashkel, so we need another way to defend our great nation. The Cowled Wizards found an answer: the Cragmyr Keep. It has a excellent location between Beregost and Nashkel, and most of all, it has a ancient Netherese Helmed Horror machine which was moved there a couple centuries ago. It is unoperational for now, but I believe I will be able to fix it when I get my hands on the documents. 

What I need from you is another matter however. You have lived in Baldur's Gate for a long time and are trusted there, so I need you to help me orchestrate a trade block on Craggmyr and make the Flaming Fist take all the blame. With the Flaming Fist discredited, I have a better chance to make Lord Kuldak choose an alliance with Amn, not Baldur's Gate and the Flaming Fist. 

Cowled Wizards, and Amn, need that machine and your help. I already inquired from our mutual hidden "friend" and he would be prepared to provide any necessary enchantment spells. Dear sister, the future of Amn and our homeland is in your hands.

Your brother~



@196 = ~Shroud of Bankao~
@197 = ~Believed to be the burial shroud of a mysterious eastern warlord, the Shroud of Bankao has been by some of the most notorious thugs and murderers on the Sword Coast. Its coarse black fabric has grown coal gray over many years of use. Its last known owner was Polger Carallo, an extortionist who operated in the worst parts of Waterdeep. Polger made his living shaking down the residents of the poor districts of the city. A priest of Bane told Polger that he owned the church a tribute for his success. Polger refused the priest's offer and died at the end of the Banite's morningstar.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
